    <bridgehead>Second Edition</bridgehead>
    
    <para>
        <personname><firstname>Nina</firstname><surname>Dubinsky</surname></personname> originated the idea to
        republish the book, and scanned a copy of the original edition provided by
        <personname><firstname>Dovid</firstname><surname>Malenkovich</surname></personname>.
        <personname><firstname>Michael</firstname><surname>Partensky</surname></personname>
        and <personname><firstname>Isaac</firstname><surname>Mushinsky</surname></personname>
        encouraged the project.</para>
    
    <para><personname><firstname>Aryeh Leyb</firstname><surname>Dubinsky</surname></personname> converted the
        content to <code>DocBook</code>.
        <personname><firstname>Menucha Rochel</firstname><surname>Dubinsky</surname></personname>assisted with
        proofreading.</para>
    
    <para><personname><firstname>Avrohom Hillel</firstname><surname>Weissman</surname></personname> made available,
        from his personal archives, questions on Parshas Yisro, Mishpatim,
        Pinchas, Shoftim and Vayikra that were missing from the original edition of the book, as well as questions on
        Parsha Bereishis that were included with some copies of the book.
        <personname><firstname>Michael</firstname><surname>Partensky</surname></personname>transcribed these
        additions.</para>

